
## COREY REMAP REFERENCE (REVISION v2.0)## [ THE THREE-ZONE ARCHITECTURE ]
Philosophy: Split the pad into Left-Side Traversal/Momentum, Right-Side Pure Violence, and a Digital Vertical Axis for non-combat admin. No input bloat. No hard lock-on required.
------------------------------
## LEFT SIDE: TRAVERSAL & MOMENTUM (VECTOR MANAGEMENT)

* L1 (Hold): Dedicated Sprint / Kinetic Accelerator. Keeps thumb completely free to steer vectors on the Left Stick.
* Left Stick: 360-Degree Directional Movement.
* Circle (Ground Context): Manual Slag Slide / Launchpad Clutch. Tapping Circle while touching a Slag patch pops the kinetic clutch, storing and converting vertical falling speed into horizontal launch velocity.
* Circle (Air Context): Traversal Grapnel Swing. Fires an anchor line dead-ahead along the camera reticle vector. No enemy targeting logic, no target-switching friction.

## RIGHT SIDE: COMBAT & CHIMAERA VIOLENCE

* R2: Fire Active Gun Weapon Mode.
* Triangle: Contextual Heavy Payload (Distance = Rocket Launcher / Melee = Vault). Melee distance instantly triggers the Vault—drives the rig blade into the anomaly, pole-vaults over its head, and dumps the rocket payload downward to blast Corey into sky-high orbit.
* Square: Hazmat Grenade Deployment (Element determined by Right Stick flick quadrant).
* Cross: Jump / Aerial Hover Jets.
* L2: Asset Morph (Tap) / Sniper Bullet-Time (Hold).

------------------------------
## DIGITAL AXIS: JOB ADMINISTRATION (UP = LIFE / DOWN = DEATH) [1] 
Horizontal axis (Left/Right) is completely VACANT. Infinite ammo removes the reload command. Axis is stripped down to prevent panicked diagonal misclicks during high-stress encounters.

* D-Pad UP: Healing Stim (The Panic Save)
* Ergonomics: Fastest, shortest linear path for the left thumb escaping upward from the stick.
   * Psychology: Upward motion equals life-bar elevation.
* D-Pad DOWN: Contextual Action (Interact / Rip Armor)
* Ergonomics: Downward pull matches the physical weight of a heavy kinetic rip or structural smash.
   * Systemic Priority Logic:
   * Priority 1: If a staggered anomaly is in melee range -> Trigger Visceral Armor Rip / Executive Execution.
      * Priority 2: If standing next to a world object -> Trigger Universal Interact (Vending Machines / Doors / Terminals).
      * Priority 3: On dry ground away from targets -> Null / No action (prevents dead frames). [2] 
   
